Just like that. Moving on to where we are right now. So things aren't that bleak, right? Yes, we have a lot to keep up with. We have a lot to keep track of. But again, to stop being so bleak and to talk about one of the reasons that we can keep up, it's because of the preexisting tools libraries and modules, particularly in Python, that help us navigate through this craziness. It's stuff that you can build on top of. And I'm sure that for a lot of these different modules and libraries, we can't really imagine our lives without them today. And building these are the struggles that we skipped.

